3098\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juni 13, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vnq1665702861307.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vnq1665702861307.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vnq1665702861307.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vnq1665702861307\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Dynamic Server Pages for the Mobile Devices\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"vnq1665702861307__dynamic_server_pages_for_the_mobile_devices_91518\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Dynamic server page (DSP) components enable you to develop responsive user interfaces for web applications and mobile apps.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vnq1665702861307__p_d27836e1_d27837e1_d27838e1\">Uniface DSPs have features that are especially designed for mobile device support:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vnq1665702861307__li_d14123e1_d14124e1_d14125e1\">Mobile App Layout—a framework that controls how content, menus, and navigation tools are defined for rendering on multiple devices, and a mechanism for binding these to DSP components. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wun1665702755914.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wun1665702755914.html\" title=\"Each mobile platform has its own user interface and interaction conventions, which affect the layout of a mobile application. The Mobile App Layout is a framework that maps HTML elements in a DSP layout to generic layout definitions.\">Mobile App Layout</a>.\n            </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vnq1665702861307__li_d14126e1_d14127e1_d14128e1\">HTML5 controls—most DSP widgets are implemented as HTML5 controls and support CSS3 styles, enabling superior rendering in mobile web browsers. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sno1665702583691.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sno1665702583691.html\" title=\"Widget definitions for Dynamic Server Pages (DSPs) are used to generate the HTML elements and controls used to represent fields, labels, occurrences, and entities displayed in the client browser.\">Widgets for Dynamic Server Pages</a>.\n            </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vnq1665702861307__li_d14129e1_d14130e1_d14131e1\">Custom class attributes—cascading stylesheets enable you to dynamically style the data. Uniface enables you to add your own class attributes to the HTML it generates for the user interface so that you can entirely customize the styling. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fjp1665702589680.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fjp1665702589680.html\" title=\"The name of a class to be dynamically added to (or removed from) the list of classes specified by the class attribute of a bound HTML element.\">class:ClassName</a>.\n            </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vnq1665702861307__li_d14132e1_d14133e1_d14134e1\">Syntax error elements and styles—you can customize syntax error handling. Bound error elements can be inserted into web layouts to display syntax errors, and pre-defined styles enable you to display and style those errors as desired. This makes it possible to handle errors differently on mobile devices than in web applications. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aqh1665702590886.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aqh1665702590886.html\" title=\"Uniface always performs server-side syntax checks when data in a dynamic server page (DSP) is validated or stored. It is also possible to perform browser-side syntax checks, so that errors are flagged before incorrect data is submitted to the server.\">Syntax Checking in Dynamic Server Pages</a>.\n            </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vnq1665702861307__li_d14135e1_d14136e1_d14137e1\">QR code generation for DSP URLs—in the Uniface IDE, you can generate a QR code for the DSP's URL, so that you can scan and run the DSP on your preferred mobile device. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"txt1665702779095.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/txt1665702779095.html\" title=\"During development you can test the user interface on mobile devices by scanning a QR code for the URL of the dynamic server page.\">Testing DSPs on Mobile Devices</a>.\n            </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ull1704691217498.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Dynamic Server Pages</a><p>Dynamic Server Pages(DSP) components define the user interface of web pages that can be incrementally and dynamically updated. They can be used in rich interactive web applications and in cross-platform mobile apps.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zrw1665702750469.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Constructing Components and Other Objects</a><p>During the construction phase of application development activity, you create development objects that define the application components and runtime libraries needed for the application. Application components can reuse definitions that you created in the modeling phase.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533098\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533098\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Dynamic Server Pages for the Mobile Devices Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juni 13, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Dynamic Server Pages for the Mobile Devices Dynamic server page (DSP) components enable you to develop responsive user interfaces for web applications and mobile apps. Uniface DSPs have features that are especially designed for mobile device support: Mobile App Layout—a framework that controls how content, menus, and navigation tools are defined for rendering on multiple devices, and a mechanism for binding these to DSP components. For more information, see Mobile App Layout . HTML5 controls—most DSP widgets are implemented as HTML5 controls and support CSS3 styles, enabling superior rendering in mobile web browsers. For more information, see Widgets for Dynamic Server Pages . Custom class attributes—cascading stylesheets enable you to dynamically style the data. Uniface enables you to add your own class attributes to the HTML it generates for the user interface so that you can entirely customize the styling. For more information, see class:ClassName . Syntax error elements and styles—you can customize syntax error handling. Bound error elements can be inserted into web layouts to display syntax errors, and pre-defined styles enable you to display and style those errors as desired. This makes it possible to handle errors differently on mobile devices than in web applications. For more information, see Syntax Checking in Dynamic Server Pages . QR code generation for DSP URLs—in the Uniface IDE, you can generate a QR code for the DSP's URL, so that you can scan and run the DSP on your preferred mobile device. For more information, see Testing DSPs on Mobile Devices . Related Links Dynamic Server Pages Dynamic Server Pages(DSP) components define the user interface of web pages that can be incrementally and dynamically updated. They can be used in rich interactive web applications and in cross-platform mobile apps. Constructing Components and Other Objects During the construction phase of application development activity, you create development objects that define the application components and runtime libraries needed for the application. Application components can reuse definitions that you created in the modeling phase. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}